三、我的觀點：<BR>
For me, the best part of this story is how the author describes the will to live. Jane was giving up her life when she was trapped in a small attic with no signal and a psychopath with a knife outside, until she remembered how much she wanted to successfully raise a child and how much effort she had made to get pregnant. So, she immediately got herself up and gathered all her strength to defeat an armed full-grown man. But can the mind really be so mighty that it can overcome physical limitations?  <br />
<br />
To find out whether people could fortify themselves to live until a certain date, such as a major holiday (ex: New Year’s Day) or event (the person’s birthday), researchers looked at millions of people’s death records and compared the numbers of death before a major holiday to the numbers after the holiday or event. The results came out that people like to enjoy holidays, so they die more often after the actual holiday. So, after the holiday the mind would assume that they have gotten to the finish line, and it’s okay to die. As a result, this research proved that people can have an extremely powerful will to live and it is evident that the mind can overcome the body’s physical limitations.<br />
<br />
I strongly agree that the will to live can be very strong as long as we have the right mindset and a positive attitude. Jane survived, because she wanted to live; lots of patients lived much longer than their doctors’ expectation, because they wanted to live. They all have an image of a better future in their mind, so they put much effort in surviving. People will always fight for a better future. But have you ever wondered why will people believe in having “a brighter tomorrow ”, when no one can predict it? Why does kids want to grow up when they don’t even know what adulthood is like? Apparently, people are blessed with positivity, and will have faith in the future. <br />
<br />
Positivity is one of the most essential things in our lives, without it, we won’t see any point of living in this world. For instance, every day we see tons of images of famous people, we might be envious of them. But if we start to look down to ourselves, if we start to think negatively, we will only discover more and more of our faults, and feel terrible of not being successful. Without a sense of positivity, many people would probably admire the talents of geniuses, such as Einstein or Newton, and thought how worthless and stupid they are, feeling that life is a total joke. But that is so not true, life will be a blessing as long as we look at this world with a correct point of view. <br />
<br />
Of course there are achievements that we can’t achieve, and there are things that we can’t change. However, if we sit down and think closely, we’ll realize how blessed we are. We complain about how tiring school is when some dreamt to go to school; we throw away food that we dislike when some are starving; we moan about walking too much when some can’t even walk. Live is about celebrating what we have, not mourning what we don’t have. Because having a good life is as simple as one two three when we know how to be thankful.<br />
<br />
Buddha once said “All that we are is the result of what we have thought.” Whenever we show gratitude for the food to eat, friends and family to talk to, a house to live in, a few challenges to keep us alive, we assume that we are happy and satisfied. In fact, we only need three things to live an enjoyable life: some money, time, and friends and family. Money to buy physical things, time to relax, and friends and family to share our joy. I believe everyone who has these three things will live a quality life. Since we can never change anything by protesting, why don’t we face the future with a positive mind starting now?<br />
<br />

